Dagannoth Prime spawns and roams on the north-eastern side of the Dagannoth Kings' lair. The lair is accessible via the [[Kings' ladder]] deep within the [[Waterbirth Island Dungeon]]. A separate lair where players that have a Dagannoth [[Slayer task]] can attack the Kings is accessible by using the "Slayer" option on the ladder. The lair can be peeked at to see if other players are inside it via the ladder and a [[Crack (Waterbirth Island Dungeon)|crack]] inside a safe room nearby the ladder.

==Strategy==
{{Main|Dagannoth Kings/Strategies}}
Dagannoth Prime, like the [[combat triangle]] suggests, is weak to [[Ranged]] attacks. The [[Zaryte crossbow|Zaryte]], [[Armadyl crossbow|Armadyl]], [[Dragon hunter crossbow|Dragon hunter]], [[Dragon crossbow|dragon]] and [[rune crossbow]]s are effective weapons against him. The [[toxic blowpipe]] is also effective, especially on a [[Slayer task]]. Wealthier players may opt to use the [[bow of Faerdhinen]] or [[twisted bow]] due to their high accuracy and damage, especially the twisted bow with its effectiveness against monsters with a high [[Magic]] level. The [[crystal bow]] is also fairly effective.

His attack is very powerful and more potent than the other two kings; it can deal up to 50 damage in one hit, so [[Protect from Magic]] prayer is a must whenever Prime is attacking. The attack is also AoE-based; any other players stood in a 3x3 tile radius around the main target will also be hit. Meleers are advised to stay away from Dagannoth Prime at all costs and fend off [[Dagannoth Supreme]] meanwhile, as Prime can kill any player not using the Protect from Magic prayer within a couple of attacks and is resistant to non-Ranged attacks.

The most effective way to kill Prime is to stand in the north-east corner of the lair while not being under attack by the other two kings, staying out of their attack radius.

If players get too close to [[Dagannoth Rex]] when they are fighting Dagannoth Prime, they may inadvertently gain Rex's attention, potentially resulting in unnecessary damage. This can be avoided by staying on the western part of the arena, as Rex will rarely (if ever) go there. [[Dagannoth Supreme]] may respawn while fighting Prime. Supreme can be avoided by staying in the north-eastern part of the arena by the seaweed. Players will want to use the "Long-range" style with their [[Ranged]] combat unless the player is sure that they will not get the attention of Supreme. Prime, along with his fellow king Supreme, have a very long-ranged attack, and if both of them focus on one player, the high damage can lead to a quick death. Players should either kill Supreme or leave the area if they find themselves under attack from both Prime and Supreme.

